[5]
Date: Fri 14 Feb 2003
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: World He lath Organisation (WHO) Disease Outbreaks Report,
Fri 14 Feb 2003 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2003_02_14/en/>

Acute respiratory syndrome in China - WHO Update 2
--------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Health, China, has reported that the outbreak in
Guangdong Province is clinically consistent with atypical pneumonia.
Cases had been detected in the province as far back as 16 Nov 2002.
The majority of the patients have experienced non-specific symptoms
including fever, headache, joint ache, and overall fatigue and
weariness. As of 11 Feb 2003, a total of 305 cases and 5 deaths have
been reported. National authorities report that outbreak is coming
under control. Investigations carried out by the Chinese authorities
have ruled out anthrax, pulmonary plague, leptospirosis, and
haemorrhagic fever.
--
